-- в”Ђв”Ђ Cloudmersive в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Cloudmersive is a developer-focused API platform offering more than 1,000 functions across security, document conversion, image processing, and data validation, all accessible through a single API key. Founded in 2017 and based in Pleasanton, California, it serves more than 1,100 businesses with capabilities such as virus scanning, PII redaction, file format conversion, OCR, and barcode generation. The service is offered on a freemium basis with a free tier and several paid tiers scaled by organization size.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium with tiered subscription plans segmented by organization size (Small Business, Medium Business, Enterprise, Government) plus a paid entry tier for individual developers$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free plan available (600 API calls per month); paid plans start at $19.99 per month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2017, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Small (exact headcount not publicly disclosed; a startup-sized team serving 1,100-plus business customers)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Pleasanton, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Cloudmersive API Platform Review 2026: Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Cloudmersive offers 1000-plus APIs for security, document conversion, image processing and validation. See 2026 pricing, features, pros, cons and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Cloudmersive, LLC is an API-first software company based in Pleasanton, California, in the San Francisco Bay Area, founded in 2017 by a team of engineers and product and business people with backgrounds in Silicon Valley. The company builds and operates a very large portfolio of utility APIs, reported to exceed 1,000 individual API endpoints, that developers can call from a single account and a single API key rather than integrating a separate vendor for each capability. The API portfolio spans several major categories. Security APIs include real-time virus and malware scanning of files and email attachments using continuously updated threat signatures, AI-based phishing detection for emails and documents, detection and redaction of sensitive data such as personally identifiable information (PII), protected health information (PHI), and financial data, a Content Disarm and Reconstruction (CDR) API that strips potentially unsafe active content out of documents and rebuilds a clean file, and AI-based spam and fraud detection. Document conversion APIs allow conversion between formats including DOCX, PDF, HTML, XLSX, PPTX, CSV, JSON, and XML, along with URL-to-screenshot capture, document editing, and tabular data processing; a related Document AI API extracts structured data and insights from unstructured documents using machine learning. Image recognition and processing APIs cover image classification, object detection, not-safe-for-work content detection, face detection, and general image editing, filtering, and resizing. Validation APIs check the legitimacy and formatting of emails, phone numbers, domains, IP addresses, and postal addresses, which developers commonly use to clean form submissions and reduce fraud. Additional APIs cover barcode and QR code generation and recognition, speech-to-text and text-to-speech conversion in multiple languages, and video and audio conversion and editing. Cloudmersive reports serving more than 1,100 of the world's largest businesses and is available through self-serve signup as well as through cloud marketplaces such as Microsoft Azure and AWS, and via low-code connectors including a Microsoft Power Automate and Logic Apps connector for document conversion. Pricing follows a freemium model: the free tier includes 600 API calls per month with a limit of 1 concurrent request, sufficient for testing and very light production use, while paid plans begin at 19.99 dollars per month for higher call volumes and concurrency. Beyond the entry-level paid tier, Cloudmersive segments its subscription plans by customer size and deployment need: Small Business plans, for organizations with fewer than 50 employees, offer basic security capabilities on a multi-tenant cloud; Medium Business plans, for organizations under 250 employees, add single-tenant cloud and on-premises deployment options, advanced security, and service level agreements; and Enterprise and Government plans support unlimited employees, multiple deployment models including government cloud, and enhanced support, all priced on a custom quote basis. Because the platform bundles so many distinct API categories under one subscription, it is frequently used by development teams that would otherwise need to integrate five or more separate point-solution vendors for tasks like virus scanning, file conversion, and data validation.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '0189a1f5-a99e-48bb-8a88-9f97971e7210';

